'''内衣外穿'''是一种受名人、体育界和媒体界推崇的{{tsl|en|fashion trend|时尚潮流}}，最初随着[[T恤|T恤]]和[[比基尼泳衣|比基尼泳衣]]等实用舒适服饰种类的诞生出现，但后来演变成饱受争议、被认为有挑衅性的时尚宣扬。到了21世纪，这种类型的女性版本会展示[[丁字裤|丁字裤]]和[[胸罩|胸罩]]，男性版本展示[[垮裤|低腰裤]]下的[[男式内裤|男式内裤]]。而早在16世纪至17世纪，内衣外穿便有历史先例<ref>{{cite web|title=Underwear as outerwear|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/magazine/7689554.stm|publisher=BBC News|author=Lisa Jardine|date=2008-10-24|accessdate=2010-02-05|archive-date=2020-11-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109042357/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/magazine/7689554.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 历史 ==
内衣外穿潮流正式出现的时间尚不明确，不过，1920年代[[香奈儿|香奈儿]]发明了由{{tsl|en|jersey (布料)|泽西布}}制造的女性内裤，而这种布料一般用于制造[[内衣|内衣]]<ref>{{cite web |title=From Marlon Brando to Kendall Jenner, 27 of the Best Classic White T-Shirts Ever |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/best-classic-white-t-shirts-of-all-time |website=Vogue |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20200707155303/https://www.vogue.com/article/best-classic-white-t-shirts-of-all-time |archivedate=2020-07-07 |date=2015-05-20 |dead-url=no |accessdate=2020-10-04 }}</ref>。后来众所周知，另一个内衣外穿的知名版本随着[[第二次世界大战|第二次世界大战]]后[[T恤|T恤]]被发明出现<ref name="Burton">{{cite web |author1=monty |title=History of the T-Shirt {{!}} Men's T-Shirt Style Ideas {{!}} Burton |url=https://www.burton.co.uk/blog/history-of-the-t-shirt/ |website=Burton |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20200707153621/https://www.burton.co.uk/blog/history-of-the-t-shirt/ |archivedate=2020-07-07 |date=2018-09-05 |accessdate=2020-10-04 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。短袖衬衫最初被看作维多利亚风格内衣的舒适替代品，但一部分青少年受了[[占士·甸|占士·甸]]和[[马龙·白兰度|马龙·白兰度]]等人分别在《[[阿飛正傳_(1955年電影)|阿飞正传]]》和《[[欲望号街车_(1951年电影)|欲望号街车]]》等电影中的穿衣影响，将衬衫外穿<ref name="Burton"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.filmsite.org/stre.html |title=A Streetcar Named Desire – AMC filmsite |publisher=Filmsite.org |date=1947-12-03 |accessdate=2010-10-26 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120802125457/http://www.filmsite.org/stre.html |archivedate=2012-08-02 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[文艺复兴|文艺复兴]]前期，[[比基尼泳衣|比基尼泳衣]]等[[泳衣|泳衣]]一开始被当成外衣<ref>{{cite book|author=Stephanie Pedersen|title=Bra|url=https://archive.org/details/brathousandyears0000pede|p= [https://archive.org/details/brathousandyears0000pede/page/8 8]|publisher= David & Charles|year= 2004|isbn=0-7153-2067-X}}</ref>，而由分层的[[雪纺|雪纺]]、[[聚酯|聚酯]][[色丁|色丁]]和{{tsl|en|charmeuse|软缎}}制造，一般用蕾丝修边的[[吊带裙|吊带裙]]于{{tsl|en|1990s in fashion|1990年代服饰|1990年代}}首次广泛穿着<ref>{{cite book|title=The Greenwood encyclopedia of clothing through American history 1900 to the present|year=2008|publisher=Greenwood Press|location=Westport, Conn.|isbn=9780313358555|page=229|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rQCEF-tG77AC&pg=RA1-PA229#v=onepage&q&f=false|editor=Amy T. Peterson & Ann T. Kellogg}}</ref>。

[[File:ExpressYourselfUnderGround_cropped.jpg|thumb]]
在娱乐界，[[摔跤|摔跤手]]和[[马戏|马戏演员]]的制服一般为内衣样式的服装；前[[DC漫画|DC漫画]]编辑{{tsl|en|Julius Schwartz|朱利叶斯·施瓦兹}}表示这就是[[超人|超人]]等超级英雄把内裤穿在外衣上面的原因<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hiskey |first1=Daven |title=Why Superheroes Wear their Underwear on the Outside |url=http://www.todayifoundout.com/index.php/2013/12/superheroes-wear-underwear-outside/ |date=2013-12-26 |website=Today I Found Out |accessdate=2020-10-04 |archive-date=2020-11-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201123193627/https://www.todayifoundout.com/index.php/2013/12/superheroes-wear-underwear-outside/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。随后，[[麦当娜|麦当娜]]掀起了女歌手舞台表演时[[女式内衣|内衣]]外穿的潮流，后来被[[碧昂丝|碧昂丝]]、[[Lady_Gaga|Lady Gaga]]、[[布兰妮·斯皮尔斯|布兰妮·斯皮尔斯]]等人模仿<ref>{{cite web|title=Underwear as outerwear|url=https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2009/nov/29/lingerie-beyonce-lily-allen-rihanna|author=Alice Fisher|date=2009-11-29|publisher=The Observer|accessdate=2010-02-05|registration=yes|archive-date=2019-04-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190410051125/https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2009/nov/29/lingerie-beyonce-lily-allen-rihanna|dead-url=no}}</ref>。当时，[[让-保罗·高缇耶|让-保罗·高缇耶]]为麦当娜的{{tsl|en|Blond Ambition World Tour|金发雄心世界巡回演唱会}}设计了“[[束腹|束腹]]”（90年代初服装的象征式标志）<ref>San Martin, Macarena (2011). Fashion Details: 1,000 Ideas from Neckline to Waistline, Pockets to Pleats. page 6. Rockport Publishers. {{ISBN|978-1-5925-3716-7}}.</ref>、一款[[神奇胸罩|锥形文胸]]和{{tsl|en|girdles|束腰带}}<ref>{{cite web |last1=Dana |first1=Rebecca |title=Lady Gaga, Katy Perry, Madonna: Dueling Cone Bras |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/lady-gaga-katy-perry-madonna-dueling-cone-bras |work=[[每日野獸|The Daily Beast]] |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20200707204756/https://www.thedailybeast.com/lady-gaga-katy-perry-madonna-dueling-cone-bras |archivedate=2020-07-07 |date=2010-06-15 |accessdate=2020-10-04 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>Steele, Valarie. “The Hard Body A Muscular Corset.” The Corset: A Cultural History. New Haven & London: Yale UP, 2001. 143-176. Print</ref>。男性方面，[[垮裤|垮裤]]（连同滑雪板）一般被认为由1990年代的说唱嘻哈艺人推崇<ref>"Teens' Sagging Jeans Not Just for 'Gangstas.'", Jennifer Skordas, Salt Lake Tribune. 15 October 1995 (p. B1).</ref>。

1968年的[[性革命|性革命]]运动中，受伦敦[[朋克文化|朋克文化]]和[[哥德次文化|哥德次文化]]影响的年轻女性，开始将束腰改为反叛和“性怪异”的标志。这次的变化，使得曾经被认为是压迫女性的束腰，摇身变成女性赋权的服装标志<ref>{{cite journal|last=Wilkins|first=Amy|title="So Full of Myself as a Chick": Goth Women, Sexual Independence, and Gender Egalitarianism|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_gender-society_2004-06_18_3/page/328|journal=Gender and Society|volume=18|issue=3|date=June 2004|pages=328–49|jstor=4149405|doi=10.1177/0891243204264421|citeseerx=<!-- 10.1.1.413.9162 -->}}</ref>。除了[[恋内衣|恋内衣]]，束腰也出现在晚礼服和结婚礼服上<ref>Crane, Diana. “Postmodernism and the Avant-Garde: Stylistic Change in Fashion Design.” Modernism/Modernity, 4, (1997), 123-140.</ref>。

=== 运动装 ===
在不同服装品牌推陈出新的助推下，T恤衫最终成为运动装<ref name="Burton"/>。1975年，[[运动胸罩|运动胸罩]]首次出现，自此成了女性的首选<ref name=komar/>。但在[[1999年国际足联女子世界杯|1999年国际足联女子世界杯]]{{tsl|en|1999 FIFA Women's World Cup Final|1999年国际足联女子世界杯决赛|决赛}}中，[[美国国家女子足球队|美国队]]的{{tsl|en|Brandi Chastain|布兰迪·查斯顿}}凭借在[[点球大战|点球大战]]中射入第五球战胜[[中国国家女子足球队|中国队]]。庆祝胜利时，查斯顿突然脱下衬衣，露出运动胸罩。部分人认为她的举动是推动运动胸罩的历史性事件<ref name=komar>{{cite web |last1=Komar |first1=Marlen |title=The Surprising Feminist History Of The Sports Bra Will Make You Seriously Angry |url=https://www.bustle.com/p/the-history-of-the-sports-bra-is-surprisingly-feminist-68920 |website=Bustle |accessdate=2019-03-22 |archive-date=2020-10-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201011011524/https://www.bustle.com/p/the-history-of-the-sports-bra-is-surprisingly-feminist-68920 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Distillations">{{cite journal |last1=Roberts |first1=Jacob |title=Women's work |journal=Distillations |date=2017 |volume=3 |issue=1 |pages=6–11 |url=https://www.sciencehistory.org/distillations/magazine/womens-work |accessdate=2018-03-22 |archive-date=2018-03-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180323154959/https://www.sciencehistory.org/distillations/magazine/womens-work |dead-url=no }}</ref>。自那时起，运动胸罩开始逐渐被人外穿<ref name=krucoff>{{Cite news|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1999/aug/09/health/he-63977|title=Sports Bras Are a Bust for Some|last=Krucoff|first=Carol|date=1999-08-09|work=Los Angeles Times|access-date=2009-09-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090406170555/http://articles.latimes.com/1999/aug/09/health/he-63977|archive-date=2009-04-06|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 文化影响 ==
[[File:ViajesinPantalones2015_26.JPG|thumb]]
社会通常将外穿内衣的民众超现实主义、搞笑。[[无裤日|无裤日]]在许多西方国家是年度活动，这一天民众公开外穿内裤，暴露双腿。类似的活动是{{tsl|en|No Pants Subway Ride|地铁无裤日}}，还有{{tsl|en|Undie Run|内衣一族跑}}活动。

踏入21世纪，[[低腰裤|低腰裤]]的普及让{{tsl|en|whale tail|鲸尾巴}}意外流行，女生们立志穿着“凸显臀部”的服装<ref>{{cite news |title=Celebrities Are Showing Off Butt Cleavage - ABC News |url=https://abcnews.go.com/GMA/story?id=125903&tqkw=&tqshow=GMA&page=1 |accessdate=2006-01-06 |work=ABC News |date=2002-07-25 |archive-date=2020-12-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201216115310/https://abcnews.go.com/GMA/story?id=125903&tqkw=&tqshow=GMA&page=1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，但是男性们穿垮裤却影响了相当大的争议，部分美国城镇甚至将这种行为当成猥亵，勒令停止<ref>{{cite news |last=Siddique |first=Haroon |date=2007-06-14 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/usa/story/0,,2103190,00.html |title=US town bans saggy pants |work=[[衛報|The Guardian]] |publisher={{tsl|en|Guardian Media Group||Guardian Media Group}} |accessdate=2007-06-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Schneiderman|first=R.M.|title=Ad Campaign Asks Queens Bus Riders to Pull Up Their Pants|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/metropolis/2010/05/17/ad-campaign-asks-queens-bus-rider-to-pull-of-their-pants/|accessdate=2010-05-28|newspaper=[[华尔街日报|The Wall Street Journal]]|agency=Metropolis (blog)|date=2010-05-17|archive-date=2020-08-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200809060456/https://blogs.wsj.com/metropolis/2010/05/17/ad-campaign-asks-queens-bus-rider-to-pull-of-their-pants/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。终于，随着2000年代末{{tsl|en|High-waisted jeans|高腰牛仔裤|高腰}}服饰的出现，鲸尾巴这一趋势终结<ref>{{cite news|first=Alex|last=Kczynski|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2004/09/12/fashion/12THON.html|title=Now You See It, Now You Don't|publisher=Fashion & Style|work=New York Times|date=2004-09-12|accessdate=2008-10-30|quote=Certainly, American clothing designers are now embracing a more modest look, their focus shifting from low-slung jeans and exposed midriffs to high-waisted trousers and cardigans.|archive-date=2015-05-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150528044256/http://www.nytimes.com/2004/09/12/fashion/12THON.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

但是男性的服装就没有经过这样的反弹，男生若是穿高腰裤，会被人嘲笑，说是在穿{{tsl|en|Dad jeans|老爸款牛仔裤}}<ref>{{Cite news| author=Associated Press| title=Obama: No apologies for 'dad jeans'| newspaper=[[芝加哥太陽報|Chicago Sun Times]]| date=2009-07-21| url=http://www.suntimes.com/news/politics/obama/1676604,w-obama-all-star-mom-jeans-072109.article| accessdate=2013-02-05| dead-url=yes| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100302222804/http://www.suntimes.com/news/politics/obama/1676604,w-obama-all-star-mom-jeans-072109.article| archivedate=2010-03-02}}</ref>。内衣公司注意到男生喜欢将裤子拉到臀部地方，这样坐着的时候低腰裤就会落到内裤下面，穿紧身裤的男性便可以暴露他们内衣的{{tsl|en|waistband|腰带}}<ref>{{cite web |title=Underwear shows more than you think: Underwear Matters - AskMen |url=https://uk.askmen.com/top_10/entertainment/top-5-reasons-underwear-matters_5.html |website={{tsl|en|AskMen||AskMen}} |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20200704234721/https://uk.askmen.com/top_10/entertainment/top-5-reasons-underwear-matters_5.html |archivedate=2020-07-04 |dead-url=no |quote=Men tend not to wear their trousers around their waists anymore, especially when it comes to jeans. Low-rise jeans are made to sit on your hips and this leaves the waistband of your underwear exposed. Your underwear is more visible than you think; the slight bend over or lift of your arms can show the world what you're rocking down there. |accessdate=2020-10-04 }}</ref>，于是在设计腰带时采用亮色和更大的标志<ref name=WWD>{{cite news |title=Underwear Waistbands: A Peekaboo Fashion Trend - WWD |url=https://wwd.com/fashion-news/fashion-features/underwear-waistbands-make-a-fashion-trend-2098105/ |work=WWD |date=2009-04-09 |accessdate=2020-10-04 |archive-date=2020-10-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201020123316/https://wwd.com/fashion-news/fashion-features/underwear-waistbands-make-a-fashion-trend-2098105/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[卡爾文·克雷恩|Clavin Klein]]内衣创意设计者鲍勃·马佐利（Bob Mazzoli）2009年解释称：“腰带虽是功能性组件，却是营销平台和实际设计时的画布......有些人将牛仔裤拉到腰部以下，将内裤露出来，引起其他人注意，已经成了我们民间文化风俗的一部分，我们在设计过程中就要考虑到这一点。”[[2(x)IST|2(x)ist]]的创意总监杰森·斯卡拉蒂（Jason Scarlatti）补充：“这是顾客[[吹嘘|吹嘘]]的权利，就好像在说，‘我为此花了很多钱’<ref name="WWD"/>。”Jockey是公认的首个将商标印在腰带上的内衣品牌，该公司于2013年启动营销活动，模特们拉起衬衫，展示牛仔裤和短裤上的Jockey腰带<ref>{{cite web |title=Are You Ready to Show You're Jockey? |url=https://www.jockey.com.ph/blogs/news/9275267-are-you-ready-to-show-youre-jockey |date=2013-05-17 |quote=Ever noticed guys with low-riding jeans deliberately showing their briefs’ waistband? Not the peeking type? Well, Jockey is. And they’ve turned this into a campaign. Jockey, inventor of the men’s Y-Front briefs and the first to use a branded waistband, launched their “Show You’re Jockey” campaign last Wednesday, May 15 at the Society Lounge in Makati City. The worldwide campaign will feature men and women of different nationalities revealing their Jockey underwear. |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131128084653/http://www.jockey.com.ph/blogs/news/9275267-are-you-ready-to-show-youre-jockey |archivedate=2013-11-28 |accessdate=2020-10-04 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

